## 16. AWS COST ANOMALY DETECTION

### Concept:
Cost Anomaly Detection continuously monitors your costs and usage using 
Machine Learning to detect unusual spends automatically.

### Key Features:

✓ Continuously monitor costs using ML
✓ Detect unusual spends automatically
✓ Learns YOUR unique spending patterns
✓ Detects:
  - One-time cost spikes
  - Continuous cost increases
✓ NO need to define thresholds (ML does it!)

### What You Can Monitor:

✓ AWS services
✓ Member accounts (Organizations)
✓ Cost allocation tags
✓ Cost categories

### Alerts:

ANOMALY REPORT:
- Root-cause analysis
- What caused the anomaly
- Impact on your costs

NOTIFICATION OPTIONS:
- Individual alerts (immediate)
- Daily summary
- Weekly summary
- Via Amazon SNS

### Architecture:

```
ANOMALY DETECTION FLOW:

┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐
│  AWS Cost        │ ──→ │ Create Cost     │ ──→ │   Get Alerted   │ ──→ │ Analyze Root  │
│  Anomaly         │     │ Monitor         │     │                 │     │ Cause         │
│  Detection       │     │                 │     │ Receive alerts  │     │               │
│                  │     │ Identify unusual│     │ when unusual    │     │ Analyze the   │
│ Reduce cost      │     │ spend at the    │     │ spend is        │     │ root cause    │
│ surprises with   │     │ granularity     │     │ detected        │     │ behind the    │
│ Machine Learning │     │ that you        │     │                 │     │ anomaly and   │
│                  │     │ specify         │     │                 │     │ the impact    │
│                  │     │                 │     │                 │     │ on your costs │
└──────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └───────────────┘
```

### Real-Life Example:
Think of Cost Anomaly Detection as a CREDIT CARD FRAUD ALERT:

CREDIT CARD FRAUD DETECTION:
- Learns your spending patterns
- Detects unusual purchases
- Alerts you immediately
- You didn't set rules, ML did

COST ANOMALY DETECTION:
- Learns your AWS spending patterns
- Detects unusual AWS costs
- Alerts you immediately
- You didn't set thresholds, ML did

### Example Scenarios:

DETECTED: One-time spike
- "EC2 costs increased by 500% on Tuesday"
- Root cause: Someone launched 50 instances
- Impact: $2,000 additional spend

DETECTED: Continuous increase
- "Data transfer costs increasing 20% weekly"
- Root cause: New application with high bandwidth
- Impact: $500/month increase

### Daily Use Cases:

