## 22. INSTANCE SCHEDULER ON AWS

### Concept:
Instance Scheduler is an AWS solution (not a service) deployed through 
CloudFormation that automatically starts/stops AWS services to reduce costs.

### Key Features:

✓ AWS solution deployed via CloudFormation (not a native service)
✓ Automatically start/stop AWS services
✓ Reduce costs by up to 70%
✓ Example: Stop EC2 instances outside business hours

### Supported Resources:

✓ EC2 instances
✓ EC2 Auto Scaling Groups
✓ RDS instances
✓ Cross-account resources
✓ Cross-region resources

### How It Works:

SCHEDULES MANAGED IN DYNAMODB:
- Define schedules (business hours, weekends, etc.)
- Store in DynamoDB table

USES RESOURCE TAGS:
- Tag resources with schedule name
- Scheduler reads tags
- Stops/starts based on schedule

LAMBDA FOR EXECUTION:
- Lambda function checks schedules
- Stops/starts instances
- Runs periodically

### Architecture:

```
INSTANCE SCHEDULER ARCHITECTURE:

┌─────────────────┐
│  CloudFormation │ (deploys solution)
└────────┬────────┘
         │
         ▼
┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐
│  DynamoDB       │────→│    Lambda       │────→│  EC2 Instances  │
│  (Schedules)    │     │  (Scheduler)    │     │  (Tagged)       │
└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘
                               │
                               │
                        ┌──────┴──────┐
                        │             │
                        ▼             ▼
                  RDS Instances   Auto Scaling
                   (Tagged)        Groups
```

### Schedule Examples:

BUSINESS HOURS:
- Start: 8 AM Monday
- Stop: 6 PM Friday
- Savings: 70%

DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT:
- Start: 9 AM weekdays
- Stop: 7 PM weekdays
- Off on weekends
- Savings: 65%

### Cost Savings Example:

```
WITHOUT SCHEDULER:
10 EC2 instances × $0.10/hour × 24 hours × 30 days = $720/month

WITH SCHEDULER (10 hours/day, weekdays only):
10 EC2 instances × $0.10/hour × 10 hours × 22 days = $220/month

SAVINGS: $500/month (70%)!
```

### Real-Life Example:
Think of Instance Scheduler as AUTOMATIC OFFICE LIGHTS:

WITHOUT SCHEDULER:
- Lights on 24/7
- Wasting electricity
- High bills

WITH SCHEDULER:
- Lights on during business hours
- Automatic off at night
- Automatic off on weekends
- Lower bills

### Daily Use Cases:

✓ Dev/Test Environments: Stop outside work hours
✓ Non-Production: Stop on weekends
✓ Batch Processing: Start only when needed
✓ Cost Optimization: Significant savings
✓ Multi-Account: Centralized scheduling

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                              SUMMARY & RECAP
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Service Quick Reference:

INFRASTRUCTURE AS CODE:
- CloudFormation = Declarative infrastructure templates

EMAIL & MARKETING:
- SES = Transactional/marketing emails
- Pinpoint = Full marketing campaigns with segmentation

SYSTEMS MANAGEMENT:
- Session Manager = Secure shell without SSH
- Run Command = Execute commands across instances
- Patch Manager = Automated patching
- Maintenance Windows = Scheduled maintenance
- Automation = Runbooks for common tasks

COST MANAGEMENT:
- Cost Explorer = Visualize and analyze costs
- Cost Anomaly Detection = ML-based unusual spend detection

HYBRID CLOUD:
- Outposts = AWS infrastructure in your data center

BATCH PROCESSING:
- AWS Batch = Long-running batch jobs (no time limit)
- Lambda = Short tasks (15 min limit)

DATA INTEGRATION:
- AppFlow = SaaS to AWS data transfer

APP DEVELOPMENT:
- Amplify = Full-stack web/mobile app development

COST OPTIMIZATION:
- Instance Scheduler = Auto start/stop resources

### Exam Tips:

✓ CloudFormation = Infrastructure as Code, templates, stacks
✓ SES = Email service, DKIM, SPF
✓ Pinpoint = Marketing campaigns, segmentation, multi-channel
✓ Session Manager = No SSH, no port 22, IAM-based
✓ Run Command = Execute across multiple instances
✓ Patch Manager = Automated OS/app patching
✓ Maintenance Windows = Scheduled maintenance tasks
✓ Automation = Runbooks for common tasks
✓ Cost Explorer = Visualize costs, forecast, savings plans
✓ Cost Anomaly Detection = ML detects unusual spending
✓ Outposts = AWS in your data center
✓ Batch = Long-running jobs, Docker, no time limit
✓ Lambda = Short tasks, 15 min limit, serverless
✓ AppFlow = SaaS to AWS integration
✓ Amplify = Full-stack app development
✓ Instance Scheduler = Start/stop resources on schedule

